  <TITLE>&quot;Email must be valid&quot; error for valid email with a four-character top-level domain</TITLE>
  <DESCRIPTION>Version: Latest Docker When attempting to create a new user that has a four-character top-level domain in the email address, an &quot;E-mail must be valid&quot; error is returned. For example, the email test@test.live is said to be invalid. However, I was able to sign up with that email, without seeing any errors. Steps to Replicate Create a new user with a four-character TLD in the email such as &quot;test@test.live&quot; Sign out Try to sign back in Observe the &quot;E-mail must be valid&quot; message What is Expected? The Email is valid per RFC spec and should be allowed.</DESCRIPTION>
